        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 13 at 8:03PM EDT by NWS Charleston WV</headline>
        <description>At 803 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 11
miles west of Mcarthur, moving northeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Allensville and Eagle Mills.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
